# Cursor Rule – progress.md Generator

## 1. Golden Rules
- One phase per `##` heading.  
- Keep each phase ≤ 30 lines.  
- Every task must start with `- [ ]` checkbox.  
- Every test line must contain the word `test` and a file path or function name.  
- Append only – never edit previous phases once marked `✅ Done`.
- Update README.md at the end of final phase.

## 2. Phase Template (copy-paste → fill)

```markdown
## Phase <N>: <Short Title>

Purpose: <One-line why this phase exists>

Tasks:
- [ ] <Task 1> (e.g., scaffold FastAPI app)
- [ ] <Task 2> (e.g., add SQLite connection)
- [ ] <Task 3> (e.g., create URLMapping model)

Unit Tests:
- [ ] test_<module>.py::<function_name> – <what is asserted>

Integration Tests:
- [ ] test_<endpoint>.py::<test_name> – <HTTP status & payload check>

✅ Done: <YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM>